Class Char2ShortMaps.EmptyMap

java.lang.Object
it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.chars.AbstractChar2ShortFunction

All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
Char2ShortSortedMaps.EmptySortedMap
Enclosing class:
Char2ShortMaps
public static class Char2ShortMaps.EmptyMap extends Char2ShortFunctions.EmptyFunction implements Char2ShortMap, Serializable, Cloneable
An immutable class representing an empty type-specific map.

This class may be useful to implement your own in case you subclass a type-specific map.

    • char2ShortEntrySet

      public ObjectSet<Char2ShortMap.Entry> char2ShortEntrySet()
      Description copied from interface: Char2ShortMap
      Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

      This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Map.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

      Specified by:
      char2ShortEntrySet in interface Char2ShortMap
      Returns:
      a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.
